Package com.poesys.db.col

Interface Summary
IColumnVisitor A Visitor pattern abstract visitor interface that has one visit method for each ColumnValue data type; this structure permits the implementation of a concrete comparison visitor that encapsulates all the logic for an operation on multiple elements of the ColumnValue class hierarchy, removing the need for separate operation implementations in the subclasses that downcast the input to the data type.
 

Class Summary
AbstractColumnValue Represents a name-value pair consisting of a column name and a column value corresponding to a data value from a database.
BigDecimalColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a BigDecimal value.
BigIntegerColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a BigInteger value.
ColumnNameComparator A Comparator implementation that compares AbstractColumnValue objects by column name instead of using the default comparison by value.
CompareColumnVisitor Implements the IColumnVisitor Visitor pattern interface to do a compareTo operation on two objects of the same type.
DateColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a Date value (no time).
IntegerColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains an Integer value.
LongColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a Long value.
NullColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a BigInteger value.
StringColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a String value.
TimestampColumnValue A concrete ColumnValue that contains a Timestamp value (date and time).
UuidColumnValue A column value containing a value of type UUID, the Java version of a globally unique identifier (GUID).
